metadata.name: COLUMNS
metadata.comment: The columns of tables defined in this database that are accessible to the current user's role.

TABLE_CATALOG.name: TABLE_CATALOG
TABLE_CATALOG.comment: Database that the table belongs to

TABLE_SCHEMA.name: TABLE_SCHEMA
TABLE_SCHEMA.comment: Schema that the table belongs to

TABLE_NAME.name: TABLE_NAME
TABLE_NAME.comment: Table that the column belongs to

ORDINAL_POSITION.name: ORDINAL_POSITION
ORDINAL_POSITION.comment: Ordinal position of the column in the table

IS_NULLABLE.name: IS_NULLABLE
IS_NULLABLE.comment: 'YES' if the column may contain NULL, 'NO' otherwise

CHARACTER_MAXIMUM_LENGTH.name: CHARACTER_MAXIMUM_LENGTH
CHARACTER_MAXIMUM_LENGTH.comment: Maximum length in characters of string columns

CHARACTER_OCTET_LENGTH.name: CHARACTER_OCTET_LENGTH
CHARACTER_OCTET_LENGTH.comment: Maximum length in bytes of string columns

NUMERIC_PRECISION_RADIX.name: NUMERIC_PRECISION_RADIX
NUMERIC_PRECISION_RADIX.comment: Radix of precision of numeric columns

COLLATION_NAME.name: COLLATION_NAME
COLLATION_NAME.comment: The name of collation, if present

IS_IDENTITY.name: IS_IDENTITY
IS_IDENTITY.comment: Whether this column is an identity column

IDENTITY_GENERATION.name: IDENTITY_GENERATION
IDENTITY_GENERATION.comment: Whether an identity column's value is always generated or only generated by default.  Snowflake only supports BY DEFAULT

IDENTITY_CYCLE.name: IDENTITY_CYCLE
IDENTITY_CYCLE.comment: Whether the value of an identity column may cycle.  Snowflake only supports NO CYCLE.

IDENTITY_ORDERED.name: IDENTITY_ORDERED
IDENTITY_ORDERED.comment: Whether the identity column is backed by an ordered sequence

SCHEMA_EVOLUTION_RECORD.name: SCHEMA_EVOLUTION_RECORD
SCHEMA_EVOLUTION_RECORD.comment: The record of the latest schema evolution of the column, if present
